From c5f320e6e3099c5539efbaf9a5937fee8971fdfc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 19:56:01 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add `runs prune` subcommand for safe cleanup of
 old runs (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add `flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N> [--dry-run]`
that deletes the oldest run directories under `<dir>/runs/` so at most N
most-recent runs remain, ranked by run start time from the replayed
journal. Strict, conservative safety rules:

- never delete a run whose replayed status is non-terminal;
- never delete the run referenced by `runs/.lock` (corrupted lock aborts);
- a missing/unreplayable `journal.jsonl` counts as non-terminal (kept) and
  is reported as skipped with its reason.

New `src/state/prune.ts` reuses the existing run-folder helpers
(`getRunDir`, `replayRunJournal`, `defaultLockPath`/`readLockInfo`, and the
now-exported `isTerminalStatus`) — no path/replay/lock logic duplicated. It
splits a pure `planPrune` policy from the `collectRuns`/`pruneRuns` I/O so
selection is unit-testable. `cli.ts` adds `parseRunsPruneArgs` + a `runs`
dispatcher + `--help` listing; no new dependencies.

Docs: register FR-E83 in the SRS (06-distribution-and-housekeeping +
index map + docs index) and SDS (design-engine 03-subsystems §3.8).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
