+### 3.8 Run Pruning (`state/prune.ts`) — FR-E83
+
+Housekeeping for old run directories under `<workflowDir>/runs/`, exposed as
+the CLI subcommand `runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N> [--dry-run]`
+(`cli.ts::parseRunsPruneArgs` + `runRuns` dispatch). All run-folder knowledge
+is reused from `state/` — no path/replay/lock logic is duplicated.
+
+- **`collectRuns(workflowDir)`:** enumerates subdirectories of
+  `dirname(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))` (the `runs/` root). For each it calls
+  `replayRunJournal(getRunDir(id, workflowDir))`; success yields
+  `{startedMs: Date.parse(state.started_at), terminal: isTerminalStatus(...)}`,
+  a `Deno.errors.NotFound` yields `unreplayableReason: "journal.jsonl missing"`,
+  any other replay error yields `"... unreplayable: <msg>"`. The locked run id
+  is read once via `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(...))`; an unreadable (present,
+  corrupted) lock rethrows so pruning fails safe. Absent `runs/` ⇒ `[]`.
+- **`planPrune(runs, keep)` (pure):** ranks replayable runs newest-first
+  (tie-break run-id desc); the `keep` newest are kept by recency; older ranked
+  runs are deleted iff terminal AND unlocked, else skipped (`non-terminal` /
+  `locked`). Unreplayable runs are excluded from ranking and always skipped
+  ("when in doubt, keep"). `--keep 0` ⇒ empty window ⇒ all terminal unlocked
+  deleted.
+- **`pruneRuns(...)`:** runs the plan, `Deno.remove(..., {recursive:true})` per
+  delete entry unless `dryRun`, and returns a `{deleted, kept, skipped, dryRun}`
+  summary that `formatPruneSummary` renders for the CLI. Tests:
+  `state/prune_test.ts`, `cli_test.ts`.
