+# `runs prune` — safe cleanup of old run directories
+
+## Goal
+
+Add a `flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N>` subcommand that
+deletes the OLDEST run directories under `<dir>/runs/` so that at most `N`
+most-recent runs remain, ranked by run start time recovered from each run's
+replayed `journal.jsonl`. Deletion obeys strict, conservative safety rules:
+never touch a run that is still active or referenced by the run lock, and treat
+any run whose journal cannot be replayed as unknown-state (keep). A `--dry-run`
+flag previews deletions without removing anything. Reuse the existing
+`src/state/` run-folder helpers — do not re-implement path construction, journal
+replay, or lock parsing.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+- A run's only durable record is `<runDir>/journal.jsonl` (append-only). Status
+  and start time are obtained by replaying it with `replayRunJournal` in
+  `src/state/run-journal.ts`. No other state source exists (no `state.json`).
+- Run-folder path helpers live in `src/state/state.ts`
+  (`getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)` → `<workflowDir>/runs/<run-id>`) and the
+  per-workflow lock lives at `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`
+  (`src/state/lock.ts`: `defaultLockPath`, `readLockInfo`, `LockInfo.run_id`).
+- `RunState.status` ∈ `running | completed | failed | aborted`. Terminal =
+  `completed | failed | aborted` (private `isTerminalStatus` in
+  `run-journal.ts`). Anything else (incl. a run still in progress) is
+  non-terminal and untouchable.
+- The CLI (`src/cli.ts`) dispatches subcommands (`run`, `answer`, `init`,
+  `mcp`) in the `import.meta.main` block; each has a dedicated arg parser
+  (e.g. `parseAnswerArgs`) that supports both `--flag value` and `--flag=value`.
+
+### Current State
+
+- No `runs` subcommand exists; `src/cli.ts:printUsage` lists only
+  `run`/`init`/`answer`/`mcp`.
+- No helper enumerates run directories under a workflow's `runs/` root, and no
+  retention/deletion logic exists anywhere.
+- `deno task check` is green at HEAD and must stay green
+  (`scripts/check.ts`: fmt, lint, type-check, CLI smoke, gitleaks, tests,
+  doc-lint, publish dry-run, docs token budget, FR canonical field-set,
+  comment scan).
+
+### Constraints
+
+- **No new dependencies.** Only Deno built-ins + already-imported `@std/path`.
+- **Reuse existing `src/state/` helpers** for all run-folder knowledge:
+  `getRunDir`, `defaultLockPath`/`readLockInfo`, `replayRunJournal`, and the
+  terminal-status classification. Do NOT duplicate the `<dir>/runs/<id>` path
+  shape, the lock-file format, or the replay logic.
+- Follow the existing `src/cli.ts` arg-parsing style (dedicated parser,
+  `--flag`/`--flag=` forms, clear error + non-zero exit on bad input).
+- `--keep` must be a non-negative integer; reject anything else.
+- `--dry-run` deletes nothing and exits 0.
+- Safety (hard): never delete a non-terminal run; never delete the run named by
+  an existing `runs/.lock`; a missing/unreplayable journal counts as
+  non-terminal (keep) and is reported as skipped with its reason.
+- Selection logic must be unit-testable in isolation (pure function) plus
+  integration-tested on temp-dir fixtures with engine-shaped journals.
+- `deno task check` stays green; register the requirement as FR-E83 in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md` (+ index
+  map in `documents/requirements-engine.md` and a row in `documents/index.md`),
+  respecting the per-file docs token budget (06 file has ~1 KB headroom).
+- Out of scope: no `runs list`/inspection output beyond the prune summary; no
+  remote/cloud cleanup; no interactive prompts.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/state/prune_test.ts` | `deno task check`) `runs prune
+      --keep N` deletes the oldest terminal, unlocked runs so the N newest
+      remain, ranked by replayed-journal start time.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/state/prune_test.ts` | `deno task check`) Non-terminal
+      runs are never deleted regardless of `--keep`.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/state/prune_test.ts` | `deno task check`) The run named by
+      an existing `runs/.lock` is never deleted (reported skipped: locked).
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/state/prune_test.ts` | `deno task check`) A run with a
+      missing or unreplayable `journal.jsonl` counts as non-terminal (kept) and
+      is reported as skipped with that reason.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/state/prune_test.ts` | `deno task check`) `--keep 0`
+      deletes all terminal unlocked runs.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/state/prune_test.ts` | `deno task check`) `--dry-run`
+      deletes nothing and exits 0; summary lists would-be deletions.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/cli_test.ts` | `deno task check`) Invalid/missing `--keep`
+      (negative, non-integer, absent) is rejected with a clear error and
+      non-zero exit; `--workflow` required.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `src/cli_test.ts` | `deno run -A src/cli.ts --help`) `runs
+      prune` appears in CLI `--help` output.
+- [x] (FR-E83 | `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md` | `deno task check`)
+      FR-E83 section added to SRS (+ index map + docs index row); docs token
+      budget respected.
+
+## Solution
+
+Variant **B (architecturally-correct)**: a pure selection function plus an
+I/O orchestrator in `src/state/prune.ts`, with `src/cli.ts` reduced to arg
+parsing + dispatch. Rationale: only this split makes the required selection
+unit tests clean and reuses every `src/state/` run-folder helper without
+duplication; Variant A entangles policy with I/O, Variant C is out-of-scope
+generality.
+
+### Retention semantics (decision)
+
+"At most `N` most-recent runs remain" is interpreted over the set of runs whose
+journal is **replayable** (only those have a comparable start time):
+
+1. Replayable runs are ranked by replayed `started_at`, newest first
+   (tie-break: run-id descending, for determinism).
+2. The `N` newest occupy the **keep window** → kept by recency.
+3. Ranked runs OLDER than the window are deletion candidates: deleted iff
+   terminal AND unlocked; otherwise **skipped** with a reason
+   (`non-terminal` / `locked`) — safety overrides the count, so an untouchable
+   run may remain even though it sits in the deletion zone.
+4. Runs whose journal is missing/unreplayable have no comparable start time →
+   excluded from ranking, always **skipped** (counted as non-terminal,
+   "when in doubt, keep"), reported with the failure reason.
+
+This satisfies every stated rule: keeps N newest, skips non-terminal, skips
+locked, missing/unreplayable ⇒ kept, `--keep 0` ⇒ all terminal unlocked deleted
+(empty window). A corrupted (unreadable, present) `runs/.lock` aborts the prune
+with a clear error (cannot determine the protected run → fail safe).
+
+### Files
+
+- **New `src/state/prune.ts`:**
+  - `ClassifiedRun` (runId, optional `startedMs`, `terminal`, `locked`,
+    optional `unreplayableReason`).
+  - `planPrune(runs: ClassifiedRun[], keep: number): PrunePlanEntry[]` — pure;
+    implements the ranking/window/zone rules above. `PrunePlanEntry =
+    { runId, action: "delete"|"keep"|"skip", reason }`.
+  - `collectRuns(workflowDir): Promise<ClassifiedRun[]>` — enumerate
+    subdirectories of `dirname(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))` (the `runs/`
+    root, derived from the lock helper, not a duplicated literal); for each,
+    `replayRunJournal(getRunDir(id, workflowDir))`. Success ⇒ classify status
+    via the (now exported) terminal-status helper + `Date.parse(started_at)`
+    (NaN start time ⇒ treated as unreplayable, "run start time unparseable");
+    `Deno.errors.NotFound` ⇒ reason "journal.jsonl missing"; other throw ⇒
+    "journal.jsonl unreplayable: <msg>". Locked id read once via
+    `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))`; corrupted lock (non-NotFound)
+    rethrows. Missing `runs/` root ⇒ `[]`.
+  - `pruneRuns({workflowDir, keep, dryRun}): Promise<PruneSummary>` —
+    `planPrune(await collectRuns(...))`, then for each `delete` entry remove
+    `getRunDir(id, workflowDir)` recursively unless `dryRun`. Returns
+    `{deleted[], kept[], skipped[{runId,reason}], dryRun}`.
+  - `formatPruneSummary(s): string` — human summary
+    (`deleted N, kept M, skipped K` + per-run skip reasons; `[dry-run]` prefix).
+- **`src/state/run-journal.ts`:** add `export` + JSDoc to `isTerminalStatus`
+  (reuse, don't duplicate the terminal set).
+- **`src/cli.ts`:** add `RunsPruneArgs` + `parseRunsPruneArgs(args)` (require
+  `--workflow`, validate `--keep` via `^\d+$`, `--dry-run`; `--flag`/`--flag=`
+  forms; clear errors). Add `runs` dispatch in `import.meta.main` → `runRuns()`
+  which routes `prune` to `pruneRuns` + prints `formatPruneSummary`; unknown
+  `runs` subcommand errors with exit 1. Extend `printUsage()` to list
+  `runs prune`.
+- **`src/state/prune_test.ts`:** temp-dir fixtures with engine-shaped journals
+  (`RunJournalWriter`) covering all DoD cases + a couple of pure `planPrune`
+  cases.
+- **`src/cli_test.ts`:** `parseRunsPruneArgs` cases (valid, `--keep=`, bad keep
+  negative/non-integer, missing `--keep`, missing `--workflow`, unknown flag).
+
+### Error handling
+
+- Bad CLI input throws inside `parseRunsPruneArgs`; `runRuns` catches, prints
+  `Error: <msg>` to stderr, exits 1 (non-zero).
+- `pruneRuns` surfaces I/O errors (e.g. corrupted lock) by throwing; `runRuns`
+  maps to exit 1.
+- Journal replay failures are caught inside `collectRuns` and converted to a
+  skip reason — they never abort the whole prune (per "when in doubt, keep").
+
+### Verification
+
+- `deno task check` (full pipeline) — must exit 0.
+- `deno test -A src/state/prune_test.ts src/cli_test.ts` during TDD.
+- Manual smoke: `deno run -A src/cli.ts runs prune --help`-style dispatch is
+  covered by the `--help` listing; `deno run -A src/cli.ts --help | grep "runs
+  prune"`.
+
+### Follow-ups (deferred)
+
+- `runs list`/inspection and age-based retention are explicitly out of scope.
+- FR-E83 SRS `**Tasks:**` back-pointer to this file is added together with the
+  new FR section (the section is authored by this task, so no deferral needed).
+
